objects.name: Text.004
objects.body_text:
Welcome to the WHIM! We hope to show you through 
this maze how difficult it is for women to navigate the 
path to accessible sexual healthcare centers. In this maze, 
you will encounter many obstacles on your way to a health
center. Check out whimteam.github.io to learn more about
each obstacle that women face, and how you can help to 
overcome these barriers. 

To move around, use the forward arrow key. The left and
right arrow keys will allow you to turn. 

Press 'p' when you're ready to begin!

objects.name: Text
objects.body_text:
Whoops! You received information in your sex education
class at high school, and didn't recieve formal education 
regarding contraception and the prevention of STIs. You
weren't taught that oral sex can lead to contraction of an STI 
and thus did not seek out medical testing after participanting 
in this activity.. Did you know that only nineteen states within 
the United States require sex education be medically accurate? 

Press "N" for the next Maze.

objects.name: Text.001
objects.body_text:
Oh no! You can't 
afford to pay for 
reproductive care, 
and you don't have
insurance that will 
cover the care that
you need.

Press N to go to
go to the next level

objects.name: Text.002
objects.body_text:
Uh-oh! You've stumbled into a 
crisis pregnancy center! While 
some of these centers provide 
quality health care, many strongly 
discourage patients from pursuing 
certain reproductive choices. In order
to do so, crisis pregnancy centers have
been reported as having provided 
inaccurate information regarding sexual
as well as having misled patients as to 
their pregnancy statuses.

Your crisis pregnancy misled you,
informing you that you were not 
pregnant. As a result, you were 
not able to receive the early prenatal
care that you needed.

Press N.
